100x32 authored geometry for Stage1.
#  solid   /  slope up-right   \  slope up-left   .  empty   S  player spawn
The text source the LDtk project was bootstrapped from (tools/export-ldtk.mjs).
Once stage1.ldtk exists, LDtk owns the geometry — this file is the pinned fixture
tests/level.test.ts checks the import against, so update it alongside real edits.
Ramps shallower than 45 degrees cannot be drawn here: a tile grid cannot say how
steep a tile is, so they are authored as Slope boxes on the Entities layer and
baked over this grid by tools/slope-bake.mjs. The cavern hills therefore show
their flat tops below but not the ramps climbing to them. Those boxes, as
run x rise tiles at their top-left tile, are:
   2x2 UpRight at  4,28
   2x2 UpLeft  at  8,28
   6x3 UpRight at 12,27
   6x3 UpLeft  at 20,27
   6x2 UpRight at 34,28
   2x2 UpLeft  at 42,28
   8x2 UpRight at 68,28
   2x2 UpLeft  at 78,28

